WHO   — Davina Vinyard — the sister in the house
WHAT  — The dissent inside the home: the family member who pushes back, and pays for it.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because not everyone in the family bends — and the film shows the price of resisting from inside.
HOW   — By arguing against Derek's bigotry and being struck for it, the household turned against its own.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I lived in that house and said no to it — and learned what saying no to your own brother's hate can cost.

